Snake Game in Python üêç
This repository contains a simple Snake Game implemented in Python using the pygame library. The classic game where the player controls a snake that grows longer as it consumes food, while avoiding collisions with itself or the boundaries.

Features:
Classic Gameplay: Control the snake using arrow keys.
Score Tracking: Score increases as the snake eats the food.
Simple Graphics: Basic, pixel-style graphics for smooth gameplay.
Game Over Condition: Ends if the snake hits the wall or itself.


how to Run:
Make sure Python is installed on your system. You can download it from here.
Install pygame by running the following command:


pip install pygame

Clone this repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/snake-game-python.git


Navigate to the project directory:
cd snake-game-python
Run the game:

python snake.py
